data.description: Incredible privacy and solitude in a fantastic location in the heart of Sarasota. Nestled on a dead-end street of only two other houses, feel as if you are set away from town but yet you are close to so much that Sarasota has to offer. This home features high ceilings and a large combination living/dining space, allowing for plenty of natural light and an open feeling. A half bath is downstairs off of the kitchen, while all three bedrooms and two full baths are upstairs allowing for privacy and quiet from the living areas. The master and another bedroom have just recently had the flooring updated and new doors added. The main bedroom comes with a sizeable walk-in closet.  Perhaps the most attractive feature of this home is the wonderful large, fully fenced backyard. With plenty of shade and already outfitted with a fire pit, this is a perfect place for entertaining, bbqs, gatherings, letting the dog(s) run about, and enjoying Florida’s year-round nice weather. So many upgrades have been down for the next owner’s peace of mind: new shingle roof that is just a year old, new AC system in 2020, new electric panel in 2015 and the Hardi-Plank cement siding was redone all around the house just three years ago. Enough cannot be said about the location: live just minutes from Sarasota’s world-famous Siesta Key and downtown, with its assortment of restaurants, shops, and the arts. One block away is Bee Ridge Park that has basketball, volleyball, softball fields and shaded playground. The school districts are amongst the most sought-after school district for elementary and middle. Schedule your showing today!
